Pennwalt Corp said it is making anew refrigerant available as an alternative tochlorofluorocarbon (CFC) 12, a product suspected of depletingthe earth's ozone layer.    The company said the new product, called isotron 142b/22,is a blend of partially halogenated CFCs, and has less thanfive pct of the ozone depletion potential of CFC 12, which isfully halogenated.    According to the company, the blend is currently used toreplace CFC 12 as a propellant in aerosol containers, and hasbeen successfully tested as a refrigerant.       Pennwalt manufactures chemicals, pharmaceuticals andprecision equipment. Reuter&#3;